Macau September Casino Revenue Rises 39% to 21.2 Billion Patacas

-- B y   B i l l y   C h a n
-- 
2011-10-04T06:26:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/macau-september-casino-revenue-rises-39-to-21-2-billion-patacas.html
Casino revenue in Macau rose 39
percent to 21.2 billion patacas in September, according to data
published on the website of the city’s Gaming Inspection and
Coordination Bureau.  Gambling revenue for the Chinese city’s casino operators
reached 194.4 billion patacas in the first nine months of the
year, 46 percent higher than a year earlier, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Billy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
 bchan101@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
